<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36218d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36218d">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36218d"> 218(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Martin Harris / David Whitmer / Oliver Cowdry</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Mormonism.]</font> A testimony signed by three witnesses, <mark>Oliver Cowdry, David Whitmer, and Martin Harris</mark>, appeared on the Book of Mormon when it was first published, solemnly declaring that these men had seen the sacred plates with the &ldquo;eye of faith,&rdquo; and with the naked eye as well. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 371</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
